result.execSummary:
The defendant Zaw Aung was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct - County Ordinance [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse]. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Affidavit of Services for Court appointed counsel and billing statement, received and filed, by Atty Voss.

Defendant Zaw Aung in court with attorney Thomas K. Voss.  Timothy Suha appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case is being called at 9:22 am. Attorney Voss states that the Defendant does not need an interpreter. Court interpreter Simon Koko appears at 9:25 as the parties did not advise the Court that an interpreter was not needed.   Prosecuting attorney moves to amend count # 2 to Disorderly Conduct contrary to section 13.102(c)(8)  of the Waukesha County Code of Ordinances.  Court approves amendment.  No contest plea entered.  Count #1 is dismissed and read-in. Court orders the following: $367.50 to be paid within 90 days or 7 days jail for penalty for non payment of fine.

Defendant Zaw Aung in court with attorney Thomas K. Voss.  Michael Thurston appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Simon Koko appears as Burmese interpreter and is sworn-in.  Attorney Voss requests an adjournment as he just received discovery and offer from the state.  Court adjourns.   Bail remains as fixed.   Interpreter available for next scheduled hearing.  Hearing scheduled for March 9, 2016 at 09:30 am.
Atty Voss has been appointed (Contract). Defendant to pay: $50/month commencing on 01/04/16.
